le=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">16</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":16,\"repo\":\"TheJambo/ToDoInterviewTest\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A very buggy To Do List to facilitate face to face interviews.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-09T08:48:03.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://amzn.to/2OERKEm\">The Scrum Field Guide, Agile advice for your first year and beyond</a> - Why you might want to move your company to Agile and great practical advice on how to do it.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-02T13:38:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://amzn.to/2AzMUF7\">Fifty quick ideas to improve your Tests</a> - Great illustrative examples on how to improve tests and why you should do them. Great as evidence for winning arguments!</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-02T13:38:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://amzn.to/2LY8ibJ\">Software Testing: An ISTQB-BCS Certified Tester Foundation guide</a> - My go to book for people brand new to testing.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-02T13:38:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://amzn.to/2n1K2aG\">Agile Testing: A Practical Guide</a> - A how to guide for those looking to transition to an Agile as a tester and also how the authors work on their Agile teams.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-02T13:38:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://amzn.to/2n8axLn\">Explore It!: Reduce Risk and Increase Confidence with Exploratory Testing</a> - A very good book on structuring Exploratory Testing and designing tests.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-02T13:38:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://amzn.to/2Az4l90\">The Domain Testing Workbook</a> - An in-depth look at the most common test technique, Domain Testing (also called Boundary Analysis and Equivalence Class partitioning) in use today with lots of examples to become better.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-02T13:38:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://amzn.to/2naYmhf\">Don't Make Me Think: A Common Sense Approach to Web Usability</a> - An incredibly useful book for usability testing.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-02T13:38:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://amzn.to/2LTjM01\">Lessons Learned in Software Testing</a> - One of the best books on Software Testing, broken into bite size lessons that are as applicable now as when it was published.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-02T13:38:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://amzn.to/2vbiALY\">UI is Communication</a> - How to make intuitive User Interfaces (UI and Usability Testing).</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-02T13:38:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://amzn.to/2vcjasX\">Thinking, Fast and Slow</a> - About how we make decisions and how to run experiments (experiments == tests).</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-02T13:38:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Software</h2><h3>Make your life easier</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/TestLinkOpenSourceTRMS/testlink-code\">TestLink</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/TestLinkOpenSourceTRMS/testlink-code\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount